s are insufficient, and a much larger number of triples are required than it was assumed so far. Still, using a commodity computer cluster, the PNO-LCCSD(T)-F12 calculation of molecules with ∼100 atoms using augmented triple-$\zeta$ basis sets can be carried out in a few hours of elapsed time.},
